@multitable {@strong{Life}} 
@item 
@strong{Life}
@end multitable

Always do right. This will gratify some people and astonish the rest.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_twain,Mark
Twain}}

A man is a success if he gets up in the morning and gets to bed at
night, and in between he does what he wants to do.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Dylan,Bob Dylan}}

Don't wait for the Last Judgement. It takes place every day.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Camus,Albert
Camus}}

Brick walls are there for a reason. They're not there to keep us out.
The brick walls are there to give us a chance to show how badly we want
something.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://randypausch.com/,Randy Pausch}}

Far and away the best prize life has to offer is the chance to work hard
at work worth doing.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theodore_Roosevelt,Theodore
Roosevelt}}

I cannot afford to waste my time making money.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Agassiz,Louis
Agassiz}}

All you have to decide is what you're going to do with the time you are
given.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf,Gandalf}}

The quality of a person's life is in direct proportion to their
commitment to excellence, regardless of their field of endeavor.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.vincelombardi.com/,Vince Lombardi}}

No art, however minor, demands less than total dedication if you want to
excel in it.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leone_Battista_Alberti,Leon Battista
Alberti}, (architect, painter and mathematician)}

My crystal ball is fuzzy@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/People/Faculty/Homepages/zadeh.html,Lotfi
Zadeh} (inventor of Fuzzy Logic, when asked to predict the future)}

If I had a dollar for every million-dollar idea I've had, I'd be rich.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://www.compliancemedia.com/Principals.html,Greg Meyer}}

There's nothing that will change someone's moral outlook quicker than
cash in large sums.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larry_Flynt,Larry
Flynt}}

The perfect is the enemy of the good.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Voltaire,Voltaire}}

I have great faith in fools. Self-confidence, my friends call it.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgar_Allan_Poe,Edgar
Allen Poe}}

The point of all this is to be able to spend more time at the beach!@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://robotics.stanford.edu/users/nilsson/bio.html,Nils Nilsson}}

Being famous has its benefits, but fame isn't one of them.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.wall.org/~larry/,Larry Wall}}

Personally, I liked the university. They gave us money and facilities,
we didn't have to produce anything! You've never been out of college!
You don't know what it's like out there! I've @emph{worked} in the
private sector. They expect @emph{results}.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000101/,Dr Ray Stanz
(Dan Aykroyd)}, Ghostbusters}

A great many people think they are thinking when they are merely
rearranging their prejudices.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_James,William
James}}

It is the mark of an educated mind to be able to entertain a thought
without accepting it.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aristotle,Aristotle}}

I try to leave out the parts that people skip.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/Elmore_Leonard,Elmore
Leonard} (on his secret to writing)}

Either write something worth reading or do something worth writing.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Franklin,Benjamin Franklin}}

Believe, if thou wilt, that mountains change their place, but believe
not that man changes his nature.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohammed,Mohammed}}

@multitable {@strong{The Universe}} 
@item 
@strong{The Universe}
@end multitable

In the beginning, the Universe was created. This has made a lot of
people very angry and been widely regarded as a bad move.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.douglasadams.com/,Douglas Adams}}

Space isn't remote at all. It's only an hour's drive away if your car
could go straight upwards.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fred_Hoyle,Fred
Hoyle}}

Man is the best computer we can put aboard a spacecraft... and the only
one that can be mass produced with unskilled labor.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://liftoff.msfc.nasa.gov/academy/history/vonBraun/vonBraun.html,Wernher
von Braun}}

We can lick gravity, but sometimes the paperwork is overwhelming.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://liftoff.msfc.nasa.gov/academy/history/vonBraun/vonBraun.html,Wernher
von Braun}}

I don't see any god up here.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gagarin,Yuri Gagarin}
(in orbit, 1961)}

Only two things are infinite, the universe and human stupidity, and I'm
not sure about the former.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Einstein,Albert
Einstein}}

There are 10@sup{11} stars in the galaxy. That used to be a @emph{huge}
number. But it's only a hundred billion. It's less than the national
deficit! We used to call them astronomical numbers. Now we should call
them economical numbers.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.feynmanonline.com/,Richard Feynman}}

For all our conceits about being the center of the universe, we live in
a routine planet of a humdrum star stuck away in an obscure corner ...
on an unexceptional galaxy which is one of about 100 billion galaxies.
... That is the fundamental fact of the universe we inhabit, and it is
very good for us to understand that.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Sagan,Carl
Sagan}}

Far out in the uncharted backwaters of the unfashionable end of the
Western Spiral arm of the Galaxy lies a small unregarded yellow sun.
Orbiting this at a distance of roughly ninety-eight million miles is an
utterly insignificant little blue-green planet whose ape-descended life
forms are so amazingly primitive that they still think digital watches
are a pretty neat idea.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.douglasadams.com/,Douglas Adams}}

@multitable {@strong{Computers}} 
@item 
@strong{Computers}
@end multitable

Some software is actually pretty good, by any standard. Think of the
Mars Rovers, Google, and the Human Genome Project. Now, that's quality
software!@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://parasol.tamu.edu/people/bs/,Bjarne
Stroustrup}, (when asked by
@uref{http://www.technologyreview.com/Infotech/17987/?a=f,Technology
Review} "Why is software so bad?". I'm proud to have worked on two of
those three projects.)}

The world has arrived at an age of cheap complex devices of great
reliability; and something is bound to come of it.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vannevar_Bush,Vannevar Bush} (1945)}

Power corrupts, and obsolete power corrupts obsoletely.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ted_Nelson,Ted
Nelson}, on the Microsoft DOS operating system}

Computers make it easier to do a lot of things, but most of the things
they make it easier to do don't need to be done@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andy_Rooney,Andy
Rooney}}

As soon as we started programming, we found out to our surprise that it
wasn't as easy to get programs right as we had thought. Debugging had to
be discovered. I can remember the exact instant when I realized that a
large part of my life from then on was going to be spent in finding
mistakes in my own programs.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maurice_Wilkes,Maurice Wilkes}}

Only wimps use tape backup: @emph{real} men just upload their important
stuff on ftp, and let the rest of the world mirror it.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linus_Torvalds,Linus
Torvalds}}

C++ is history repeated as tragedy. Java is history repeated as farce.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{mailto:swm@@mediaone.net,Scott McKay}}

Nothing is destroyed until it is replaced.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Auguste_Comte,Auguste
Comte (1798-1857)} (on the need for revolutionary new theories (or on
the need to do @code{x.f = null} in garbage-collected languages with
destructors))}

In general, they do what you want, unless you want consistency.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.wall.org/~larry/,Larry Wall} (on Perl
functions)}

Computer language design is just like a stroll in the park. Jurassic
Park, that is.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.wall.org/~larry/,Larry Wall}}

If you give someone Fortran, he has Fortran. If you give someone Lisp,
he has any language he pleases.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guy_Steele,Guy L.
Steele}}

[Lisp] is the only computer language that is beautiful.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neal_Stephenson,Neal
Stephenson}}

If you can't hear me, it's because I'm in parentheses.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steven_Wright,Steven
Wright}}

He who refuses to do arithmetic is doomed to talk nonsense.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www-formal.stanford.edu/jmc/,John
