We read Knuth so you don't have to.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -@uref{http://c2.com/cgi/wiki?TimPeters,Tim Peters}
(explaining what the Python developers do in their spare time)}

Computers are useless. They can only give you answers.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Picasso,Pablo
Picasso}}

I do not believe in objects. I believe only in their relationships.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Braque,George
Braque}}

I don't paint things. I only paint the difference between things.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matisse,Henri
Matisse}}

Mathematicians do not study objects, but relations among objects; they
are indifferent to the replacement of objects by others as long the
relations don't change. Matter is not important, only form interests
them.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henri_Poincar%C3%A9,Henri Poincare}}

Have nothing in your houses that you do not know to be useful, or
believe to be beautiful.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://www.morrissociety.org/,William Morris}}

All models are wrong. Some models are useful.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ -
@uref{http://www.engr.wisc.edu/ie/faculty/box_george.html,George Box}}

When cryptography is outlawed, bayl bhgynjf jvyy unir cevinpl!@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brad_Templeton,Brad
Templeton}}

Errors using inadequate data are much less than those using no data at
all.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Babbage,Charles
Babbage}}

In the future, search engines should be as useful as HAL in the movie
@emph{2001: A Space Odyssey}--but hopefully they won't kill people.@*
@emph{@ @ @ @ - @uref{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sergey_Brin,Sergey
Brin}}

